'''diddle''' is the spot on a guy on the front side of the underarm. It is used in conjunction with the actually torso and arm to form a pillow for other people. Guys will often use this to comfort people or make them feel safe.

+++++Definition Two+++++

A '''diddle''', in [[percussion]], is a [[rudiment]] consisting of playing a note twice with one hand. Continuously playing alternating diddles results in a [[double-stroke roll]].

==Technique==

At lower [[tempo]]s, a diddle can be achieved by simply stroking twice with the same hand. At higher tempos, [[fingersnapping]] can be used. If the tempo is too fast for the performer to fingersnap, he may let the stick bounce, risking a loss of precision.

==Notation==

On [[sheet music]], a diddle is shown by slashing the stem of a note, usually of a [[sixteenth note]].
On [[Drum tablature|tablature]], a diddle is often shown by the letter 'd' in the respective [[drum]]'s line.

